Final Project: USVI Mangrove Reproduction

Sarai Hutchinson

2024-12-05

Objectives

The aim of this project is to use the GRROE Lab’s Master Intake Data for Red Mangroves to determine:

1. How the red mangrove collection sites have changed from 2021 to 2024?

2. Around what time of the year are the red mangroves reproducing most?

3. How has reproduction changed over time?

4. Map the Collection Sites of Red Mangroves

Preparing Data

Data Set-up

Load the necessary libraries anf functions:

  1. tidyverse

  2. dplyr

  3. ggplot2

  4. lubridate

  5. writexl

  6. split_collection_date_func.R


The first step is to import the CSV for the red mangrove intake data as of November 20th, 2024 and a CSV I made with the simplified collection sites coordinates.

Data Cleaning

Then, begin performing QA/QC on the data by removing the spaces from the column headers.

It’s time to clean the data by formatting the dates to look the same for Collection Date and Date Planted. Create columns that separate the Collection Date column into Year, Month and Day.

After looking at the CollectionDate column and finding a particularly early date, the next step is to change 19/09/2002 to 19/09/2023 after verifying the raw data and the fact that this collection only began in 2021.

I then made the Collection Date to be one format and checked to see if there were any dates that failed this section.

I created a function to help me split my newly created CollectionDateParsed column into Collection Year, Collection Month and Collection Day.

Now, I have the cleaned and filtered data that I exported and used to make my maps in Arc Gis Pro.

Answering Questions

Question 1

How have the red mangrove collection sites have changed from 2021 to 2024?


This graph shows the increase in the number of red mangrove collections from 2021 to 2024. It shows that the most collections were made from Perseverance Bay in 2024.


Question 2

Around what time of the year are the red mangroves reproducing most?

This question is difficult to answer with the current data. I would need data that has the number of collectors to have an effort factor, and we would have needed to have been going to collect mangroves at each site each month to determine whether more mangrove collection is because of effort or there actually being more mangroves at each site.



The question I asked instead is what is the total number of red mangroves collected across all sites in a certain month


This bar graph shows that most mangroves were collected in September, followed by February and January. This corresponds with having more lab interns to help with collections.

Question 3

How did total number of collection dates change over the years? Did we collect more or less?
